DESCRIPTION:The Chicago Drum Circle Meetup Group\nDinner as a group at 6:00pm. (not included in price) A fantastic chance to break bread and connect to your drum community. After that\, drum lesson and 2\, 30 minute drum circles.\n\nDouble Clutch Brewery\n2121 Ashland Ave\, Evanston\, IL 60201\nThe night will start out with a Rhythm Community Dinner\nfollowed by an hour long drum lesson. You'll learn\nsome drum technique and some basic rhythms.\nThen make your own beats on the drum\, or try\nsome shakers\, wood blocks and of course MORE COWBELL!\n6:00 dinner: Grab a bite with your favorite drummer friends and be introduced to some new ones.\n7:15 Setup for drumming and get your spot\n7:30pm -8:30 drum lesson/ drum circle\n8:30-8:45 pm drink circle and socialize\n8:45-9:00 Drink Circle with Musical guest TBA\n9:00 - 9:30pm Drum Circle\n9:30pm-10:00- Drink Circle\n10:00pm-10:30 Drum Circle\n10:30 last call\nTo reserve a drum\, attend class\, and pay admission send $15 via zelle 773-802-0605 (John Yost)\nTo attend class and admission (no drum rental) send $10 via zelle 7738020605 (John Yost)\nTo pay at the door text John 7738020605
